  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency and Preparedness Response to the Spread of the Ebola Virus Epidemic #11 in DRC</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Project Aim:  

Action Against Hunger&#x202F;(AAH)&#x202F;plans to&#x202F;intervene to mitigate the spread of EVD for vulnerable populations in&#x202F;Bikoro&#x202F;and&#x202F;Boende&#x202F;health zones by strengthening their response and preparedness capacities in&#x202F;Infection&#x202F;Prevention and&#x202F;Control&#x202F;(IPC)&#x202F;practices.&#x202F; 

Firstly, in&#x202F;Bikoro,&#x202F;it&#x202F;aims at preventing further&#x202F;spread of EVD&#x202F;among AAH&#x202F;beneficiaries and health personnel in&#x202F;15&#x202F;health facilities&#x202F;currently&#x202F;supported by&#x202F;AAH&#x202F;Emergency Nutrition Response&#x202F;Team&#x202F;(Emergency Nutrition&#x202F;Program&#x202F;for Congo - PUNC).&#x202F;Then it would increase the coverage to the whole&#x202F;health&#x202F;zone, adding 6 Health Areas to the current intervention,&#x202F;for&#x202F;both Nutrition and IPC&#x202F;activities. Thirdly,&#x202F;it will&#x202F;participate to prepare&#x202F;Boende&#x202F;health&#x202F;area&#x202F;to cope with a possible occurrence of EVD cases.&#x202F;&#x202F; 
 

Outputs: 
R1.&#x202F;21&#x202F;health&#x202F;areas&#x202F;in&#x202F;Bikoro&#x202F; strengthen their IPC capacities&#x202F;and EVD screening&#x202F; 


R2.&#x202F;&#x202F;Boende&#x202F;health zone is better prepared for an IPC response in case of an EVD outbreak including the BCZ management team and personnel of 35 health facilities&#x202F; 


R3.&#x202F;Severe Acute Malnutrition prevention and treatment is strengthened in 6 health areas of&#x202F;Bikoro&#x202F; 

Beneficiary Numbers: 2,044</narrative>
  </description>
